<LegalLayout
  title="Limitations"
  description="What PatientBillGuide tools cannot detect — important limitations for bill review."
  crumbs={[
    { label: 'Methodology', href: '/methodology/' },
    { label: 'Limitations' },
  ]}
>
  <h2>We cannot see your full medical record</h2>
  <p>
    Without diagnoses, operative notes, and insurer contracts, we cannot confirm medical
    necessity or definitive upcoding. Flags are <strong>heuristic</strong>, not legal findings.
  </p>

  <h2>Benchmarks are not quotes</h2>
  <p>
    Medicare allowed amounts are public anchors. Your insurer’s negotiated rate or a hospital’s
    cash price may legitimately differ. We do not have access to your plan’s fee schedule.
  </p>

  <h2>Parser limits</h2>
  <p>
    Pasted bills and EOBs vary by format. OCR for photos is not supported in v1. Unusual
    layouts may parse incompletely — always compare to your original document.
  </p>

  <h2>Not legal or medical advice</h2>
  <p>
    Dispute letter templates are starting points. For complex disputes, balance billing law,
    or large amounts, consider professional advice.
  </p>

  <h2>Confidence levels</h2>
  <p>
    Every flag includes a confidence indicator (high / medium / low). Low-confidence items
    deserve scrutiny but not panic.
  </p>
</LegalLayout>
